PART I, LINE 4B EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2003,THE UNIVERSITY ADOPTED THE SUPPLEMENTAL RETENTION AND RETIREMENT PLAN (SERRP),AN UNFUNDED DEFINED BENEFIT RETIREMENT PLAN FOR SENIOR EXECUTIVES THE PURPOSE OFTHE PLAN IS TO REWARD PERFORMANCE, LOYALTY AND CONTINUOUS SERVICE OFTHOSE INDIVIDUALS SELECTED AS PARTICIPANTS IN THE PLAN UNDER THE TERMS OFTHE PLAN,THE UNIVERSITY WILL PAY PARTICIPANTS THE LUMP SUM EQUIVALENT VALUE OF A LIFE ANNUITY PAYING 60% OFTHE AVERAGE OFTHE PARTICIPANTS THREE FINAL CALENDAR YEARS OF BASE SALARY AND ANNUAL INCENTIVE COMPENSATION THE BENEFIT IS OFFSET FOR EMPLOYER CONTRIBUTIONS (AND RELATED EARNINGS)TO THE 403(B) SAVINGS PLAN AS WELL AS THE EMPLOYER-PROVIDED PORTION OF SOCIAL SECURITY SERRP BENEFITS VEST UPON A PARTICIPANT ATTAINING AGE 65 WITH 25 YEARS OF SERVICE ANY PARTICIPANT WHO LEAVES THE SERVICE OFTHE UNIVERSITY BEFORE REACHING BOTH OFTHESE MILESTONES IS NOT ELIGIBLE TO RECEIVE A BENEFIT FROM THE PLAN WHILE THE CHANGE IN THE PRESENT VALUE INCLUDES CHANGES IN THE DISCOUNT RATE USED FOR ACCOUNTING PURPOSES, THE ACTUAL LUMP SUM IS BASED ON A FIXED INTEREST RATE OF 6% THE AMOUNTS REPORTED IN THIS FORM 990 REPRESENT THE INCREASE IN THE PRESENT VALUE OFTHE ACCRUED BENEFIT (WITHOUT REGARD TO VESTING) THE NET INCREASE IN THE PRESENT VALUE OFTHE ACCRUED BENEFIT BY PARTICIPANT INCLUDED ON SCHEDULE J IS JACK P VARSALONA, $473,931, HEATHER A O'CONNELL, $72,201, LAVERNE T HARMON, $160,745, CAROLE D PITCHER, $77,504, PETER BAILEY $102,255, ERIN DIMARCO, $40,668 AND JAMES WILSON,JR $77,043

PART I, LINE 7 THE UNIVERSITY PROVIDES BONUSES TO THE INDIVIDUALS LISTED ON SCHEDULE J IT UTILIZES A NUMBER OF PERFORMANCE OBJECTIVES TO DETERMINE THE BONUS AMOUNTS THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OFTHE BOARD OFTRUSTEES MEETS TO SPECIFICALLY DISCUSS EXECUTIVE BONUS AMOUNTS THE COMMITTEE UTILIZES AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT THAT PROVIDES INFORMATION FROM A VARIETY OF COMPENSATION STUDIES AND SURVEYS INCLUDING 990's THE COMMITTEE FOLLOWED THE PROCESS TO ESTABLISH THE PRESUMPTION THAT COMPENSATION PAID TO THE ORGANIZATION'S PRESIDENT AND OTHER TOP MANAGEMENT FOR PURPOSES OF SECTION 4958 BY RELYING ON PROFESSIONAL ADVICE IN THE WRITTEN OPINION OF REASONABLENESS FROM THE INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT ONCE ALL OFTHIS INFORMATION IS GATHERED AND REVIEWED,THE COMMITTEE APPROVES THE BONUS FOR EACH EXECUTIVE ALL COMPENSATION,INCLUDING COMPENSATION COMMITTEE APPROVED BONUSES,ARE REPORTED TO THE FULL BOARD OFTRUSTEES
